2. Data Preprocessing

In[5]:
df = df_raw.copy()

# Convert timestamps
df['sleepStartTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['sleepStartTimestampGMT'])
df['sleepEndTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['sleepEndTimestampGMT'])
df['calendarDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['calendarDate'])

# Calculate durations in hours
df['deepSleepHours'] = df['deepSleepSeconds'] / 3600
df['lightSleepHours'] = df['lightSleepSeconds'] / 3600
df['awakeHours'] = df['awakeSleepSeconds'] / 3600
df['totalSleepHours'] = df['deepSleepHours'] + df['lightSleepHours']
df['totalTimeInBedHours'] = (df['sleepEndTimestamp'] - df['sleepStartTimestamp']).dt.total_seconds() / 3600

# Sleep efficiency
df['sleepEfficiency'] = (df['totalSleepHours'] / df['totalTimeInBedHours']) * 100

# Temporal features
df['dayOfWeek'] = df['calendarDate'].dt.dayofweek
df['dayOfWeekName'] = df['calendarDate'].dt.day_name()
df['month'] = df['calendarDate'].dt.month
df['monthName'] = df['calendarDate'].dt.month_name()
df['year'] = df['calendarDate'].dt.year
df['quarter'] = df['calendarDate'].dt.quarter

# Season
def get_season(month):
    if month in [12, 1, 2]: return 'Winter'
    elif month in [3, 4, 5]: return 'Spring'
    elif month in [6, 7, 8]: return 'Summer'
    else: return 'Autumn'

df['season'] = df['month'].apply(get_season)

# Sleep/wake times
df['sleepTimeHour'] = df['sleepStartTimestamp'].dt.hour + df['sleepStartTimestamp'].dt.minute/60
df['wakeTimeHour'] = df['sleepEndTimestamp'].dt.hour + df['sleepEndTimestamp'].dt.minute/60

# Deep sleep percentage
df['deepSleepPercent'] = (df['deepSleepHours'] / df['totalSleepHours']) * 100

# Filter OFF_WRIST
df = df[df['sleepWindowConfirmationType'] != 'OFF_WRIST'].copy()

print(f" Preprocessing complete")
print(f"Analyzed records: {len(df):,}")
print(f"Date range: {df['calendarDate'].min().date()} to {df['calendarDate'].max().date()}")

 Preprocessing complete

fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(16, 10))

# Time series
ax1 = axes[0]
ax1.plot(df['calendarDate'], df['totalSleepHours'], alpha=0.3, linewidth=0.5, color='steelblue')
df['rolling_30d'] = df['totalSleepHours'].rolling(window=30, center=True).mean()
ax1.plot(df['calendarDate'], df['rolling_30d'], linewidth=2, color='darkblue', label='30-day avg')
ax1.axhline(y=7, color='green', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Min (7h)')
ax1.axhline(y=9, color='orange', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Max (9h)')
ax1.set_xlabel('Date')
ax1.set_ylabel('Total Sleep (hours)')
ax1.set_title('Sleep Duration Timeline', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
ax1.legend()
ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Distribution

# Correlation matrix
corr_cols = ['totalSleepHours', 'deepSleepHours', 'lightSleepHours', 
             'awakeHours', 'sleepEfficiency', 'sleepTimeHour', 'wakeTimeHour']
corr_matrix = df[corr_cols].corr()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 10))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='coolwarm', 
            center=0, ax=ax, square=True, linewidths=1,
            xticklabels=['Total', 'Deep', 'Light', 'Awake', 'Eff', 'BedT', 'WakeT'],
            yticklabels=['Total', 'Deep', 'Light', 'Awake', 'Eff', 'BedT', 'WakeT'])
ax.set_title('Correlation Matrix of Sleep Metrics', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

print("\nKey Correlations (|r| > 0.3):")
for i in range(len(corr_cols)):
    for j in range(i+1, len(corr_cols)):
        r = corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]
        if abs(r) > 0.3:
            print(f"{corr_cols[i]:20s} <-> {corr_cols[j]:20s}: r = {r:6.3f}")
